        <num>CHC 1415</num>
        <heading>1415.  Burden of proof; order</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 1415.  Burden of proof; order
If the court finds by clear and convincing evidence that the minor has a mental illness or suffers from substance abuse of such severity that hospitalization is necessary and that he can benefit from inpatient treatment, it shall order his continued confinement in a designated treatment facility which is medically suitable and least restrictive of his liberty.</p>
        </content>
